ownedComment.body: Concrete subclasses should add a VersionedReference attribute with an appropriate targetClass tagged value.
When using this class, at least one "applicableDay" must be specified in class "DayWeekMonth".
timePeriodOfDay and dayOfWeek must be applicable within the specified overall time period or exception period respectively.
exceptionPeriod is a period during which validity is suspended and must be applicable within the specified overallTimePeriod.

Within each instance of this class, specific enumerated values can only be used once for all attributes. E.g. applicableMonth can only contain january once. A combination of applicableDay monday and tuesday and applicableMonth may and june results in a data set of all Mondays and Tuesday in May and June.

To specify emissionClassificationEuro properly, it is necessary to define
  • the corresponding vehicle type (e.g. car for M1, miniBus for M2, lightCommercialVehicle for N1 or largeGoodVehicle for N2)
  • and fuel type (e.g. diesel for CI engines or petrol for PI engines)
in class vehicleCharacteristics. Note that Euro V and Euro VI are used for emissions of lorries only.
